## The Answer: Passive Eavesdropping via Separate Consumer Group

Your workflow component **never needs the existing services to send it anything**. It simply **listens to the same Kafka topics** that already exist in your pipeline, using its **own independent consumer group ID**.

---

## How Kafka Consumer Groups Work

```
Existing Topic: "validator.output"
        │
        ├──── Consumer Group: "validator-service-group"    ← Your existing Validator service
        │                     (reads & processes messages)
        │
        └──── Consumer Group: "workflow-tracker-group"     ← Your NEW workflow component
                              (reads same messages, just updates state)
```

**Kafka delivers every message to EVERY consumer group independently.** Each group maintains its own offset pointer. So:

- Your existing service reads the message → does its job → moves on
- Your workflow tracker reads the **same message** → extracts bookId → updates state in DB
- Neither knows the other exists
- Neither affects the other

---

## Visualizing It End to End

```
[Source Adapter] ──publishes──→ "source.adapter.output" topic
                                        │
                    ┌───────────────────┴────────────────────┐
                    ↓                                         ↓
        "validator-group"                        "workflow-tracker-group"
        (Existing Validator Service)             (Your NEW module)
        Processes the book                       Reads bookId → sets state = RECEIVED
```

Same thing happens at every topic in your pipeline. The workflow tracker simply **taps into every topic** and updates state silently.

---

## Why This is Safe

| Concern | Answer |
|---|---|
| Will it slow down existing consumers? | No — Kafka groups are fully independent |
| Will it cause duplicate processing? | No — existing group is unaffected |
| What if workflow tracker is down? | It catches up automatically when it restarts, from its own saved offset |
| What if it falls behind? | It processes at its own pace — no impact on pipeline |

